items.name: TubeBuddy
items.details: TubeBuddy tracks your rankings and compares your analytics to those of your competition on YouTube as well as in Google searches. Also give you real-time suggestions on videos, keywords, ranking and just about everything you need to grow.

items.name: VidIq
items.details: VidIQ is a video analytics & marketing tool for Youtube publishers. This tool analyzes your Youtube account and gives you meaningful insights, monitor keyword scores, views, and other search term metrics all from one place.

items.name: Keywords Everywhere
items.details: The Keywords Everywhere browser add-on can be easily installed on either Chrome or Firefox. The best part is that we show you monthly search volume, cost per click and competition data of keywords on multiple websites.

items.name: Tuber Tools
items.details: Tubertools for youtuber where multiple resources can found like Headers, Thumbnail, Motion Graphics etc

items.name: Social Blade
items.details: Social Blade is a website that tracks social media statistics and analytics. Social Blade most notably tracks the YouTube platform, but also has analytical information regarding Twitch, Instagram, Twitter, Facebook etc

items.name: Google Docs
items.details: Google Docs is Google's browser-based word processor. You can create, edit, and share documents online and access them from any computer with an internet connection. ... Google has made it incredibly easy to share documents across platforms and work on them together in real time from a browser window.

items.name: Camtasia Video Editor
items.details: Camtasia is a professional-level video editing software. It have both Screen Record and Edit Features. The software solution provides a good balance of high-quality output, control, and a well-designed user interface, which makes the platform more suitable for web content creators/producers and videographers.

items.name: Streamlabs
items.details: Created as a utility for those who stream online video games, Streamlabs is a widget that allows its users to collect donations from their fans. The Streamlabs service works with popular platforms, such as Twitch, YouTube, Facebook Live, and Mixer.

items.name: OBS Studio
items.details: OBS is a free open source software suite that is used for recording and live streaming. OBS is used to capture and record your screen while also capturing audio

items.name: Microsoft PowerPoint
items.details: PowerPoint is allows you to create and show slides to support a presentation. You can combine text, graphics and multi-media content to create professional presentations.

items.name: YouTube Studio
items.details: The official YouTube Studio app makes it faster and easier to manage your YouTube channels on the go. Check out your latest stats, respond to comments, upload custom video thumbnail images, schedule videos, and get notifications so you can stay connected and productive from anywhere.
